 And so, man, everything problem solved.

50
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:15,100
 We would fly in that night and then fly back out.

51
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:18,300
 Like we were, you know, rock stars in Coldplay or something.

52
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:23,300
 And the day came, got to the airport, got on the plane,

53
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:25,580
 everything was going fine.

54
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:27,300
 And then we took off.

55
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:30,300
 And I quickly realized a few things

56
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,780
 that I hadn't anticipated.

57
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:33,800
 This was not Air Force One by any means.

58
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,980
 There was a reason why he was like, just cover the fuel.

59
00:02:35,980 --> 00:02:38,820
 It was like a plane from the late 70s or the 80s.

60
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:40,720
 It was tiny, it was cramped.

61
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:43,860
 And that becomes really important,

62
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:47,100
 the size or a very small two propeller plane,

63
