 with your life, ignorance really is bliss.

72
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,540
 If you're having heart surgery, you don't want to know,

73
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:15,860
 you know, the heart surgeon was your fraternity buddy,

74
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:19,060
 Frank the Tank, who barely graduated.

75
00:03:19,060 --> 00:03:22,620
 You want to assume he graduated, you know, magna cum laude

76
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:26,380
 and was nominated for the Nobel Peace Prize last year.

77
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,900
 And the pilot is also one of those situations

78
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:32,380
 where Mark was his name and he's awesome,

79
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:34,340
 but he's also kind of a little crazy.

80
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,620
 And he would always joke about like,

81
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:36,900
 man, I don't know what I'm doing up here.

82
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:38,340
 The first time flying and you're like,

83
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:39,700
 okay, it's not a good joke, man.

84
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,180
 There's a lot of storms outside.

85
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:44,740
 And he, on top of all of that,

86
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,420
 he had just recently left ministry

87
00:03:46,420 --> 00:03:47,900
 to go and help run this plane.

88
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,780
 So I'm like, bro, you've been doing this like an hour.

89
00:03:49,780 --> 00:03:52,780
 And he had nine fingers, story for another time.

90
00:03:52,780 --> 00:03:54,540
 But in the moment you're like, oh man,

91
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:56,300
 but there's at least 10 buttons up there,

92
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,540
 I know, on this plane.

93
00:03:57,540 --> 00:04:01,320
 And so it's storming and I can feel every up and down

94
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,700
 as we're flying here with these guys.

95
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:07,940
 And I'm like, oh man, this is how I go out.

96
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:09,740
 I'm going to die at the hands of nine finger Mark

97
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:12,100
 and my kids, you just run a worst case scenario

98
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:14,260
 when anxiety hits and I'm walking through like,

99
00:04:14,260 --> 00:04:16,260
 who's going to teach my son how to throw the ball?

100
00:04:16,260 --> 00:04:18,460
 Who's going to walk my daughter down the aisle?

101
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:20,860
 And just all of those thoughts internally that,

102
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,300
 people around you may not even realize,

103
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:26,940
 but they're just where anxiety has taken over.

104
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:28,060
 Now, irony of ironies,

105
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:31,640
 I was flying to college station to teach on anxiety.

106
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,060
 I'm like, I'm a total hypocrite.

107
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,560
 I'm going to die in this plane.

108
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:38,660
 But it was one of those moments when anxiety

109
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:41,180
 just grabs you, strikes.

110
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:44,060
 And what do you do in those moments?

111
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:47,460
 This is a question that is increasingly important

112
00:04:47,460 --> 00:04:51,500
 because anxiety, when it strikes in that moment,

113
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,880
 you and I have a choice,

114
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,740
 not over whether we're going to have anxious thoughts

115
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:57,420
 or feelings, but what we do with those.

116
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,820
 And as a society, we are not great

117
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:03,180
 when it comes to coping with anxiety.

118
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:05,220
 In part, because of the enormous rates

119
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:09,140
 at which it is impacting so much in so many of our lives

120
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:11,700
 and COVID didn't help that.

121
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:14,720
 In fact, recent studies from the CDC have shown

122
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:19,720
 that 63% of young people ages between 18, 30

123
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:23,940
 are suffering from significant symptoms

124
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:25,380
 of anxiety or depression.

125
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:27,060
 Nearly a quarter of respondents reported

126
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:30,400
 that they had started or increased the abuse of substances,

127
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,660
 including alcohol, marijuana, prescription drugs,

128
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:35,400
 to cope with their anxiety.

129
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:38,900
 In June, 2020, CDC released data that suggests

130
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:43,720
 one in four young adults had considered suicide.

131
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:47,860
 Here's a slide that shows the incredible growth

132
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:52,740
 that happened from 2019 and the rates of adults reported

133
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:55,060
 with symptoms of anxiety disorder

134
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,500
 and the impact COVID has had.

135
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,100
 It's just exploded.

136
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:01,700
 America is by far the most anxious nation on the planet

137
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:04,660
 before a pandemic, and it hasn't gotten any worse.

138
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:07,420
 And in particular, it's only gotten worse

139
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:08,240
 among young adults.

140
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,900
 Here's the age breakdown of people

141
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:13,700
 that have reported symptoms of anxiety disorders.

142
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:19,000
 The largest two buckets being 18 to 24,

143
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,360
 and we can safely assume the 25 to 49

144
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:26,360
 is likely more than 25 to 35 in there.

145
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,800
 And so anxiety is not just a problem,

146
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,980
 it's a problem that's getting increasingly worse.

147
00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:33,000
 And young adulthood is a time in life

148
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,400
 where there is so much change happening,

149
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,680
 it makes all the sense in the world

150
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,820
 that you would be anxious.

151
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:39,940
 What do I mean?

152
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:41,940
 Well, prior to this stage in life,

153
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:44,100
 everything was pretty clearly mapped out for you,

154
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,720
 if you think about it.

155
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,620
 Like, remember, you're in first grade

156
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:49,320
 and the tracks were laid out.

157
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:50,660
 Where do you go after first?

158
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,640
 Second grade.

159
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,480
 Where do you go after that?

160
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,360
 Third.

161
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,520
 Where do you go after middle school?

162
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:55,600
 High school.

163
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,320
 There's this clear path and track.

164
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,280
 Where do you go after high school?

165
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:02,000
 Freshman year, sophomore year, junior year, senior year.

166
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,880
 And then it's like the tracks run out

167
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:07,840
 and ah, free fall, as there isn't a clear,

168
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,680
 what is the next step?

169
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:12,380
 And a lot of people don't have wise people in their life

170
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:13,220
 to help them know, like,

171
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:14,880
 what am I supposed to do with my life?

172
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:15,800
 Am I in the right job?

173
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,680
 Am I dating the person that I'm supposed to marry?

174
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:21,240
 How am I gonna afford to pay off my student loans?

175
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,760
 And it becomes this free fall

176
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,480
 that is a breeding ground for anxiety.

177
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,560
 Makes all the sense in the world.

178
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,620
 Which is why this is one of the most anxious times,

179
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:31,640
 or anxious time periods in life.

180
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,500
 And on top of all of that,

181
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,700
 just to validate a little bit more,

182
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:39,160
 the average age of marriage in the last 20 or 30 years

183
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:43,440
 has gone from around the age of 24 and 23 to 30 and 29.

184
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:46,080
 Which means most of us are walking through

185
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:49,920
 the most anxious time in our life all alone.

186
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,080
 Which further contributes to anxiety.

187
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:55,500
 And so we're doing this series

188
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:59,400
 because we wanna help address such a huge issue.

189
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:02,560
 And candidly, I think that the church

190
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:05,480
 has done a really poor job at handling this subject.

191
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,640
 And here's what I mean.

192
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:11,080
 Intentionally or unintentionally,

193
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:12,560
 a lot of people have communicated

194
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,800
 that what the Bible says and what Christians believe

195
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,760
 is that when it comes to anxiety, you should just stop.

196
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:19,360
 If you were to ask the average Christian,

197
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,520
 hey, what do you think the Bible teaches about it?

198
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:23,920
 They have either been misinformed

199
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,880
 or are uninformed what the Bible actually teaches.

200
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,820
 So they assume it's just like,

201
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:30,000
 hey, just stop or have more faith.

202
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,960
 Which doesn't help.

203
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,360
 In other words, if saying, hey, stop it,

204
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:38,520
 actually worked, you would have just stopped.

205
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,360
 It's not helpful.

206
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,880
 It's like telling someone who can't fall asleep

207
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,840
 or struggling to fall asleep, hey, just fall asleep.

208
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,400
 And you're like, oh, thanks for the advice.

209
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,080
 And the same is true with anxiety.

210
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,160
 And tragically, that idea of the Bible just saying,

211
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,640
 hey, just stop or just pray,

212
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:57,320
 fails so largely

213
00:08:57,320 --> 00:09:01,160
 to communicate what the Bible actually teaches.

214
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,400
 And so I wanna walk through and help connect the dots

215
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,800
 on some of what the Bible teaches

216
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,460
 as it relates to fighting anxiety,

217
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,800
 because here's what's true.

218
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:11,040
 For Christians, I'm talking to Christians,

219
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:13,120
 our first line of defense

220
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:17,760
 when it comes to battling anxiety, worry, fear,

221
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,360
 is always God's word.

222
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:22,040
 That doesn't mean that things like counseling

223
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,460
 or medication or things outside of that,

224
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:25,440
 there's no place for it.

225
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,140
 Those are wonderful fields, incredible.

226
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:30,080
 My wife is a licensed counselor.

227
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,660
 I have personally benefited deeply from counseling.

228
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:36,500
 But for Christians, it does mean anything in addition

229
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:39,620
 to God's word is a supplement, not a replacement.

230
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:42,220
 The Bible is our first line of defense.

231
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:44,800
 And I think the church has not taught

232
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,340
 what the Bible actually teaches,

233
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:49,600
 which means has not given the first line of defense

234
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,440
 to followers of Christ.

235
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,340
 So that is the passion around this series

236
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:53,180
 and around this book,

237
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:56,180
 because God's word is so much more practical and helpful

238
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,500
 than maybe you have ever realized.

239
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,860
 So tonight we're gonna walk through

240
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:01,260
 just one of the teachings,

241
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:04,960
 given 2000 years ago, that is so incredibly brilliant,

242
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:08,540
 given by the son of God when he walked on this planet,

243
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:10,020
 talking to a group of people

244
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:15,020
 who turns out were struggling with anxiety.

245
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:16,220
 It's been around a long time.

246
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,740
 And Jesus brings up some principles and truths

247
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:21,980
 that are so relevant to how we

248
00:10:21,980 --> 00:10:23,660
 can experience increasing freedom

249
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:26,820
 and why everyone in the world is freaking out,

250
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:28,340
 but why we don't need to.

251
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:29,820
 So we're gonna be in Matthew chapter six.

252
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:31,220
 If you have a Bible, you can flip open.

253
00:10:31,220 --> 00:10:33,000
 These may be verses, if you grew up in church,

254
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:37,300
 you've heard before and may have never actually heard taught

255
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:41,020
 in line with what they're saying.

256
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:45,220
 And we're gonna look at five truths Jesus gives us.

257
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:48,540
 But before we go there, I wanna define anxiety biblically,

258
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,660
 'cause one of the challenges with this topic

259
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:55,100
 is people have many associations with words

260
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:58,220
 like anxiety, worry, fear,

261
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,800
 and then you throw in anxiety disorder,

262
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,220
 generalized anxiety disorder,

263
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:03,740
